convertBlackBoxToFence(25.10)                    convertBlackBoxToFence(25.10)

Name
       convertBlackBoxToFence - Converts a blackbox to a fence

Syntax
       convertBlackBoxToFence

       [-help]

       {-cell <cellName> | -inst <instName>}

       Converts  a blackbox to a fence. Once the black box netlist is well de-
       fined, use this command to convert the black box back to a regular par-
       tition.

Parameters
       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the name of a module or submodule that should be  con-
              verted to a fence.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each convertBlackBoxToFence parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man convertBlackBoxToFence

       -inst <instName>
              Specifies the name of the blackbox instance that should be  con-
              verted to a fence.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command converts a blackbox, hinst5, to a fence:

       convertBlackBoxToFence -inst hinst5

